[SN]TITLE[SN]
Paris tributes after the attacks - 360-degree video

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
At the Place de la Republique people hug, cry, lay flowers and a few sing the national anthem. The site is close to the Petit Cambodge restaurant and Le Carillon bar where gun attacks occurred last Friday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
After the Charlie Hebdo attacks in January 2015 the Place de la Republique was where a million people gathered in a show of unity.  And following last week's attacks, it is again a scene of memorial and strength.
