The deadliest attack of the night of 13 November came at a concert venue in Boulevard Voltaire, in the 11th district, where rock group Eagles of Death Metal was playing. The 1,500-seat Bataclan hall was sold out. Eighty-nine people died as attackers fired Kalashnikov-type assault rifles into the crowd. Many others are in a critical condition in hospital.
